    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Cylinder Head and Valve Train -
        Reconditioning - Inspecting Valve Rotators
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Inspecting Valve Rotators</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean all valve rotators in a suitable solvent.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650551" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5206.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Checking valve rotator</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Ram</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Steel ball bearing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Paint reference line</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve rotator</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Spring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the valve rotator with clean engine oil. Place the valve spring and rotator in
                spring tester.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a ball bearing between the valve rotator and the ram of the spring tester. The ball
                bearing must be large enough to prevent the ram from touching any part of the rotator.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Paint a reference line on the valve rotator and spring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Compress the valve spring rapidly with even pressure and observe the valve rotator as it
                turns. Replace any valve rotator that does not turn.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
